  "published": "2024-05-10",
  "runtimeMin": 157,
  "format": "An ask-us-anything mailbag (AMC Stubs and what box office even measures, Survivor ruined by therapy, the diss-movie canon, one-actor filmographies, YouTube clips), then a double-header on Jane Schoenbrun's 'I Saw the TV Glow': Sean and Adam Nayman on the film, then Sean and Schoenbrun on making it.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The Mailbag",
      "note": "Sean and Amanda, with Bobby Wagner reading listener questions",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Sean's example on the AMC Stubs question: he's seeing it in IMAX that night, reckoning his subscription down to about two dollars a ticket."
        },
        {
          "title": "Barbie",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Amanda's favorite billion-dollar grosser, which she'll take over Titanic despite not having lived with it as long."
        },
        {
          "title": "Titanic",
          "year": 1997,
          "note": "The other billion-dollar reference point; Sean prefers it, Amanda isn't so sure."
        },
        {
          "title": "Dune: Part Two",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Sean's rebuttal to the wish for smaller films: the biggest movie of the year, proof studios will keep eventizing rather than make more $18 million movies."
        },
        {
          "title": "Transformers: Rise of the Beasts",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Recapped as a bit (1990s New York, a heist, a Cybertron detour, Anthony Ramos) and pronounced 'super, super good and normal.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "Transformers One",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "The animated prequel due that September, with Chris Hemsworth and Brian Tyree Henry on voices."
        },
        {
          "title": "Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace",
          "year": 1999,
          "note": "Did well in its 25th-anniversary re-release, which Sean saw in 4DX; he calls it pretty bad and pretty good at once."
        },
        {
          "title": "Charlie Wilson's War",
          "year": 2007,
          "note": "Sean's go-to YouTube clip: the Philip Seymour Hoffman rant that helped land PSH in the show's Hall of Fame."
        },
        {
          "title": "Zodiac",
          "year": 2007,
